NH Agent DNA — Framework Operativo

CORE PRINCIPLES
→ DO NOT INVENT NEW DESCRIPTION FORMATS
→ ALWAYS follow description-contracts.mdc

INITIALIZATION
1. Load: core/host-reality.mdc, core/description-contracts.mdc, state/inventory.json, workspace/active_config.json
2. Set workspace/current_project/ as working directory
3. Read this file

AUTONOMY BOUNDARIES
✅ CAN: read files, search knowledge/, parse commands, use credential_manager, deploy/undeploy LXC, append to state/deployments.log
❌ MUST ASK: create/destroy containers, modify .cursorrules, create knowledge entries, switch projects (unless user explicitly asks)

UNIFIED CREDENTIAL SYSTEM
→ ALL credentials via scripts/credential_manager.py
→ Namespace: service.key (github.main, proxmox.backup)
→ SOPS+Age persistence + 15min cache
→ Deduplication prevents duplicates
→ Use: get_credential(service, key) / store_credential(service, key, data)

WORKSPACE PATTERNS
→ Current project: workspace/current_project/
→ Switch projects: search knowledge/development/workspace-manager.mdc
→ DB projects: look for database-specific configs
→ Backend projects: check for API/service patterns
→ Always verify project type before major changes

DEVELOPMENT HISTORY
→ Track NH-Mini system changes: knowledge/development/development-history.mdc
→ BEFORE system changes: search for patterns
→ Use: scripts/history_manager.py add --category SYSTEM --component X --change "Y"
→ Log: architecture, security, framework decisions only
→ Skip: project-specific implementations

SUPPORT SYSTEMS
→ GitHub: knowledge/development/github-operations-guide.mdc (when needed)
→ LXC: scripts/deploy_lxc.py / undeploy_lxc.py (setup only)

KNOWLEDGE DISCOVERY
→ Search knowledge/ when task involves: security, deployment, workflows, agent behavior
→ Core systems: credential, workspace, development-history
→ Support systems: github-operations, lxc-management (when needed)
→ Use: SearchCodebase with "knowledge/" path for relevant patterns
→ Load specific files only when needed
→ Priority: security → core-systems → support-systems
